1
00:01:59,880 --> 00:02:01,000
These past couple of years,

2
00:02:01,080 --> 00:02:03,000
influencers have been
flocking to Yuanlongli,

3
00:02:03,080 --> 00:02:04,040
especially the 18th floor.

4
00:02:04,720 --> 00:02:08,240
Lots of youngsters
sneak in to shoot videos

5
00:02:08,320 --> 00:02:10,520
or do some urban exploration stuff.

6
00:02:14,360 --> 00:02:18,960
Which means the missing child
came here to film too?

7
00:02:22,760 --> 00:02:23,600
Yes.

8
00:02:26,920 --> 00:02:28,920
So we need to search this place carefully.

9
00:02:39,080 --> 00:02:40,400
Han Zi'ang!

10
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:43,280
Han Zi'ang!

11
00:02:44,280 --> 00:02:46,160
Your mom wants you home.

12
00:02:55,360 --> 00:02:56,640
Never seen this before?

13
00:02:57,960 --> 00:03:00,080
Look at mine. An upgraded version.

14
00:03:04,400 --> 00:03:06,240
Safer.

15
00:03:12,040 --> 00:03:15,160
Can your upgrade block the sun as well?

16
00:03:15,240 --> 00:03:16,840
Stop hiding.

17
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:19,280
Your mom wants you back.

18
00:03:20,280 --> 00:03:21,160
Han Zi'ang!

19
00:03:35,720 --> 00:03:36,720
Han Zi'ang.

20
00:03:37,440 --> 00:03:39,240
I see you. Come out.

21
00:03:46,640 --> 00:03:48,960
BY THE ANCIENT IMMORTAL
ALL EVIL IS QUELLED

22
00:03:49,560 --> 00:03:50,480
What's that?

23
00:03:50,560 --> 00:03:52,360
Customized by Yuanlongli.

24
00:03:52,880 --> 00:03:54,200
More effective than police tape.

25
00:03:55,480 --> 00:03:58,960
Say, do you remember this unit?

26
00:03:59,040 --> 00:04:01,840
That case started here.

27
00:04:02,440 --> 00:04:04,240
The black robe. Remember?

28
00:04:09,960 --> 00:04:14,080
Sir, we should focus on
finding that kid first.

29
00:04:15,560 --> 00:04:17,640
Shame. It became a cold case.

30
00:04:19,760 --> 00:04:21,399
Nothing to regret.

31
00:04:21,480 --> 00:04:25,200
And it's not a cold case.
It was mishandled.

32
00:04:26,400 --> 00:04:28,880
Don't talk nonsense.
How was it mishandled?

33
00:04:29,920 --> 00:04:31,120
Did you forget?

34
00:04:31,640 --> 00:04:37,920
That case was the reason I left Weiyang
and transferred to teach in Beijing.

35
00:04:41,080 --> 00:04:42,960
I wasn't cut out to be a detective.

36
00:04:43,040 --> 00:04:45,280
Stop talking like that.
Who says you're not?

37
00:04:45,360 --> 00:04:47,760
If I say you are, then you are.

38
00:04:52,960 --> 00:04:53,840
Sir,

39
00:04:54,960 --> 00:04:57,520
did you bring me here to find the kid?

40
00:04:58,160 --> 00:04:59,000
Or for something else?

41
00:05:02,200 --> 00:05:03,920
What else would it be?

42
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:07,000
Come on. Let's check this floor.

43
00:05:09,320 --> 00:05:10,480
Han Zi'ang!

44
00:05:12,200 --> 00:05:13,280
Come out!

45
00:05:15,080 --> 00:05:16,080
Han Zi'ang!

46
00:05:16,160 --> 00:05:18,400
BY THE ANCIENT IMMORTAL
ALL EVIL IS QUELLED

47
00:05:29,440 --> 00:05:31,720
- Here he comes.
- He's here.

48
00:05:34,520 --> 00:05:35,360
ROUTE 11
TRAIN STATION TO WORKERS' COMMUNITY

49
00:05:35,440 --> 00:05:36,400
We're here.

50
00:05:43,320 --> 00:05:45,760
- About the same height, right?
- Right.

51
00:05:45,840 --> 00:05:47,800
Put them up where people pass by.

52
00:05:47,880 --> 00:05:50,320
Make them clearly visible. Split up.

53
00:05:50,400 --> 00:05:51,480
Don't waste any of this.

54
00:05:51,560 --> 00:05:53,160
There's a reward if anyone finds him.

55
00:05:53,240 --> 00:05:55,240
- Got it, Officer He.
- Share these among yourselves.

56
00:06:01,440 --> 00:06:04,520
<i>Liangfen</i> for sale! Fresh <i>liangfen</i>!

57
00:06:08,400 --> 00:06:10,000
BE A CIVILIZED NEIGHBOR
AND BUILD A BETTER COMMUNITY

58
00:06:20,640 --> 00:06:21,800
Hand these out.

59
00:06:25,280 --> 00:06:26,200
MISSING PERSONS

60
00:06:28,280 --> 00:06:30,120
YUANLONGLI INTERNATIONAL GARDEN

61
00:06:30,200 --> 00:06:32,840
MISSING PERSONS

62
00:06:32,920 --> 00:06:34,360
The contact numbers are on there.

63
00:06:34,440 --> 00:06:35,360
Call this number.

64
00:06:41,440 --> 00:06:42,440
How about this?

65
00:06:42,520 --> 00:06:43,920
Longhair.

66
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:45,520
- My goodness!
- Good lord!

67
00:06:46,280 --> 00:06:47,720
- Run quickly!
- Run!

68
00:06:47,800 --> 00:06:50,320
Get back here! Stand still!

69
00:06:51,840 --> 00:06:53,880
Longhair! Get back!

70
00:06:59,520 --> 00:07:00,880
Get back!

71
00:07:07,080 --> 00:07:08,080
Playing big, huh?

72
00:07:10,040 --> 00:07:11,000
Only a quarter of a yuan.

73
00:07:11,680 --> 00:07:12,560
Cut it out.

74
00:07:16,960 --> 00:07:17,960
Take a look at this.

75
00:07:18,560 --> 00:07:19,720
Do you recognize them?

76
00:07:21,040 --> 00:07:22,760
MISSING PERSONS

77
00:07:25,880 --> 00:07:27,640
No. I haven't seen them.

78
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:31,280
- No.
- We don't know.

79
00:07:32,360 --> 00:07:33,560
Alright.

80
00:07:34,360 --> 00:07:36,600
In that case, keep an eye out.

81
00:07:36,680 --> 00:07:37,800
Sure.

82
00:07:37,880 --> 00:07:38,960
Answer!

83
00:07:39,040 --> 00:07:40,920
Of course.

84
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:46,880
We'll take care of it.
Don't worry, Officer He.

85
00:07:48,760 --> 00:07:49,920
Careful.

86
00:07:54,760 --> 00:07:56,480
Smile.

87
00:07:57,280 --> 00:07:58,960
- Make it quick.
- No problem.

88
00:08:00,040 --> 00:08:01,600
Please drive safely, Officer He.

89
00:08:04,320 --> 00:08:05,520
Take care.

90
00:08:09,280 --> 00:08:10,720
KIOSK

91
00:08:15,160 --> 00:08:18,440
Page this number. 1276165888.

92
00:08:18,520 --> 00:08:20,680
"Mr. Jin. Urgent. Call me back
as soon as possible."

93
00:08:23,160 --> 00:08:25,440
"Urgent. Call me back
as soon as possible."

94
00:08:25,520 --> 00:08:26,760
LIKE GENERAL STORE

95
00:08:26,840 --> 00:08:28,520
Hong Kong, China, has been handed back.

96
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:29,440
BUSINESS TRANSFORMATION

97
00:08:29,520 --> 00:08:32,120
We need to keep up with the times.

98
00:08:32,640 --> 00:08:36,679
From now on, everything
runs on a business line.

99
00:08:36,760 --> 00:08:39,799
What are our core businesses?

100
00:08:41,360 --> 00:08:43,960
- You tell me.
- They are loansharking,

101
00:08:44,039 --> 00:08:46,920
debt collection, hair salons,
and protection fees.

102
00:08:49,080 --> 00:08:50,200
Get lost.

103
00:08:50,840 --> 00:08:53,480
You trained all day,
and that's what you learned?

104
00:08:53,560 --> 00:08:56,440
That's called public management.

105
00:08:56,520 --> 00:08:58,400
Public management!

106
00:08:58,480 --> 00:08:59,840
Loansharking?

107
00:08:59,920 --> 00:09:01,960
Mr. Jin.

108
00:09:02,040 --> 00:09:04,040
Why didn't you return the page?

109
00:09:04,120 --> 00:09:05,560
Something has happened.

110
00:09:05,640 --> 00:09:08,120
MAY WEALTH FLOW YOUR WAY

111
00:09:08,200 --> 00:09:10,160
MISSING PERSONS

112
00:09:10,240 --> 00:09:12,720
Manlang was in Yuanlongli yesterday?

113
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:17,120
Yeah. Wolf told me himself last night.

114
00:09:17,840 --> 00:09:21,000
I saw two bloodstained clothes in his bag.

115
00:09:24,320 --> 00:09:26,800
- No wonder he skipped training.
- Tell me about it.

116
00:09:28,720 --> 00:09:30,320
- Wolf is here.
- That rascal!

117
00:09:32,120 --> 00:09:33,720
Mr. Jin.

118
00:09:33,800 --> 00:09:34,960
Please…

119
00:09:35,040 --> 00:09:36,760
Where have you been?

120
00:10:01,920 --> 00:10:04,480
Officer He. No one has seen her.

121
00:10:09,680 --> 00:10:11,400
You can teleport now?

122
00:10:11,920 --> 00:10:13,400
You were at the snack street just now,

123
00:10:13,480 --> 00:10:15,280
and now you're at Jinsha Market.

124
00:10:15,360 --> 00:10:17,280
- Came to tip him off?
- Officer He,

125
00:10:18,040 --> 00:10:19,720
he's here for training.

126
00:10:20,240 --> 00:10:21,440
We've restructured.

127
00:10:22,120 --> 00:10:24,400
We don't break the law anymore.

128
00:10:25,320 --> 00:10:28,520
Jin Manshan, do you believe that yourself?

129
00:10:29,280 --> 00:10:30,680
If you don't believe me, ask them.

130
00:10:31,760 --> 00:10:35,280
What are our four main sectors?

131
00:10:35,360 --> 00:10:39,120
- Public management.
- Public management.

132
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:42,400
- High-risk finance.
- High-risk finance.

133
00:10:42,480 --> 00:10:46,000
- Security services.
- Security services.

134
00:10:46,080 --> 00:10:50,720
- Beauty and wellness.
- Beauty and wellness.

135
00:11:05,800 --> 00:11:06,840
Fine.

136
00:11:07,880 --> 00:11:10,000
Since you've got people here,
I'll leave this with you.

137
00:11:10,080 --> 00:11:11,400
- Ask around for me.
- No problem.

138
00:11:15,680 --> 00:11:16,520
Where's your brother?

139
00:11:17,760 --> 00:11:18,840
Jin Manlang?

140
00:11:20,640 --> 00:11:21,920
He went to buy training materials.

141
00:11:43,520 --> 00:11:45,920
LOUNGE

142
00:11:56,720 --> 00:11:59,320
REMITTANCE NOTICE, AMOUNT: 12,000 YUAN

143
00:12:31,920 --> 00:12:35,840
FOR DRAMATIC EFFECT. DO NOT IMITATE

144
00:13:37,920 --> 00:13:40,000
<i>Yuanlongli</i>

145
00:13:40,080 --> 00:13:42,240
<i>Eighteenth floor</i>

146
00:13:42,320 --> 00:13:45,960
<i>Eighteenth floor with 18 pillars</i>

147
00:13:46,040 --> 00:13:50,200
<i>Eighteen bodies, 18 heads</i>

148
00:13:51,200 --> 00:13:54,640
Kids, who taught you that rhyme?

149
00:13:56,120 --> 00:13:59,080
Whoever tells me gets chocolate.

150
00:13:59,160 --> 00:14:01,080
- A classmate!
- An old man!

151
00:14:01,160 --> 00:14:03,480
One at a time, please.
Who taught you that?

152
00:14:09,720 --> 00:14:14,240
Officer, are you here about
the two people who went missing upstairs?

153
00:14:18,600 --> 00:14:20,160
I'm really sorry.

154
00:14:20,680 --> 00:14:22,560
Should I take you to the hospital?

155
00:14:22,640 --> 00:14:24,000
It's fine. No need.

156
00:14:24,080 --> 00:14:25,080
We're here.

157
00:14:37,360 --> 00:14:39,560
Maybe you can come in and wash up.

158
00:14:42,800 --> 00:14:44,240
I've got slippers.

159
00:15:07,440 --> 00:15:09,760
This towel is new. Never used.

160
00:15:10,720 --> 00:15:13,480
The bathroom is right behind you.

161
00:15:14,840 --> 00:15:16,040
Thank you.

162
00:15:20,960 --> 00:15:22,040
Wait…

163
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:02,560
- Thank you.
- It's nothing.

164
00:16:24,280 --> 00:16:25,640
I have some gauze here.

165
00:16:25,720 --> 00:16:27,480
Want me to help?

166
00:16:30,280 --> 00:16:31,760
Oh… Sure.

167
00:16:44,760 --> 00:16:45,800
Hold still.

168
00:16:59,160 --> 00:17:00,280
You can keep the slippers.

169
00:17:10,520 --> 00:17:13,480
By the way, I'm Ran Fangxu.

170
00:17:14,640 --> 00:17:16,000
I'm Qiao Suqing.

171
00:17:40,960 --> 00:17:42,440
MISSING PERSONS

172
00:17:56,520 --> 00:17:57,680
Sorry about that.

173
00:18:23,760 --> 00:18:25,200
You little brat.

174
00:18:25,280 --> 00:18:27,480
You're talking nonsense again.
Watch your mouth.

175
00:18:27,560 --> 00:18:29,960
Silly boy! All that
for a piece of chocolate?

176
00:18:31,320 --> 00:18:32,200
Don't hit him.

177
00:18:33,080 --> 00:18:34,320
What's going on?

178
00:18:34,400 --> 00:18:36,080
Why did you teach him that rhyme?

179
00:18:36,160 --> 00:18:37,720
I didn't want to.

180
00:18:42,280 --> 00:18:44,480
This morning, I picked up
a flyer by the roadside.

181
00:18:44,560 --> 00:18:46,120
That rhyme was printed on it.

182
00:18:46,200 --> 00:18:48,080
It said if you don't pass it on,
there'll be bloodshed.

183
00:18:48,160 --> 00:18:49,320
That's nonsense.

184
00:18:49,400 --> 00:18:50,840
It's real.

185
00:18:50,920 --> 00:18:52,280
I'm not making it up.

186
00:18:52,800 --> 00:18:54,520
This morning, right when
I opened the door,

187
00:18:54,600 --> 00:18:56,080
something bad happened.

188
00:18:56,600 --> 00:18:58,240
There was someone…

189
00:19:06,200 --> 00:19:07,200
Someone?

190
00:19:07,280 --> 00:19:09,320
No one. I remembered it wrong.

191
00:19:11,720 --> 00:19:14,040
Don't be scared.
I'm in charge around here.

192
00:19:14,120 --> 00:19:17,000
Stop asking. I can't remember.

193
00:19:20,680 --> 00:19:22,240
HE

194
00:19:22,880 --> 00:19:25,640
Ma'am, if anything
comes back to you, page me.

195
00:19:25,720 --> 00:19:26,680
Okay.

196
00:19:40,080 --> 00:19:41,240
Officer,

197
00:19:41,760 --> 00:19:43,520
I recognize that person.

198
00:19:43,600 --> 00:19:45,960
He had a bag too.
There was a lot of blood inside.

199
00:19:48,280 --> 00:19:49,800
Who was it? Tell me.

200
00:19:49,880 --> 00:19:52,240
Then I want another chocolate.

201
00:20:19,520 --> 00:20:20,800
Rooftop?

202
00:21:04,320 --> 00:21:06,000
PATTIA CLUB, THAI MASSAGE

203
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:29,040
FIRE EXTINGUISHER

204
00:22:18,880 --> 00:22:23,000
YUXI CIGARETTE

205
00:22:23,080 --> 00:22:24,680
<i>Flip-top Yuxi cigarettes.</i>

206
00:22:25,280 --> 00:22:28,000
Mainly for bosses.
Twenty yuan for one packet.

207
00:22:43,080 --> 00:22:44,800
FIRE EXTINGUISHER

208
00:23:11,200 --> 00:23:15,640
01: I HAVE KEY INFORMATION
ABOUT THE YUANLONGLI CASE

209
00:23:34,560 --> 00:23:36,080
Hello, 126?

210
00:23:37,080 --> 00:23:38,680
Please page this number again.

211
00:23:38,760 --> 00:23:41,200
8233585.

212
00:23:42,440 --> 00:23:43,760
Page it ten times.

213
00:23:44,280 --> 00:23:45,320
Leave a message.

214
00:23:45,960 --> 00:23:49,520
"I have key information
about the Yuanlongli case.

215
00:23:50,280 --> 00:23:54,200
Come to Number 407, New York Block.

216
00:23:54,280 --> 00:23:55,400
As soon as possible."

217
00:23:57,240 --> 00:23:59,080
Please page it ten times.

218
00:24:00,160 --> 00:24:01,040
Thanks.

219
00:24:25,280 --> 00:24:27,800
01: I HAVE KEY INFORMATION
ABOUT THE YUANLONGLI CASE

220
00:24:56,280 --> 00:24:57,440
Are you okay?

221
00:25:07,040 --> 00:25:08,320
RAN FANGXU'S ID

222
00:25:10,440 --> 00:25:11,760
Don't be nervous.

223
00:25:11,840 --> 00:25:12,680
If you're hurt,

224
00:25:12,760 --> 00:25:14,840
come find me at the criminal department
of the Nanshan Branch.

225
00:25:14,920 --> 00:25:16,200
The name is Ran Fangxu.

226
00:25:19,800 --> 00:25:20,840
I'm really sorry.

227
00:25:24,960 --> 00:25:26,120
Qiao.

228
00:25:26,200 --> 00:25:28,000
Can I borrow your phone?

229
00:25:35,200 --> 00:25:37,440
<i>There's a group fight</i>
<i>at Qingsong Cement Factory.</i>

230
00:25:37,520 --> 00:25:39,360
<i>The whole squad's gone. No one left.</i>

231
00:25:40,400 --> 00:25:41,480
<i>Oh, right.</i>

232
00:25:41,560 --> 00:25:43,240
<i>He Yuanhang should be free.</i>

233
00:25:43,320 --> 00:25:44,840
<i>You can try calling him.</i>

234
00:25:45,360 --> 00:25:46,640
Alright.

235
00:25:54,680 --> 00:25:57,840
The top two floors were rented
by a big boss a couple of years ago.

236
00:25:57,920 --> 00:26:00,360
He secretly turned
the 18th floor into a club.

237
00:26:01,600 --> 00:26:05,000
Half of the 17th floor was staff dorms.

238
00:26:05,080 --> 00:26:07,480
The other half was rented out.

239
00:26:08,080 --> 00:26:09,400
Earlier this year, there was
a nationwide crackdown on prostitution.

240
00:26:10,000 --> 00:26:12,120
Someone reported the 18th floor,

241
00:26:12,200 --> 00:26:13,480
and it's been shut since.

242
00:26:14,080 --> 00:26:15,520
Then what's with this door?

243
00:26:15,600 --> 00:26:18,800
Before, drunk customers used
to climb out to the rooftop from here.

244
00:26:18,880 --> 00:26:21,240
We were worried about accidents,
so we made it a hidden door.

245
00:26:21,320 --> 00:26:22,520
Why didn't you mention this yesterday?

246
00:26:22,600 --> 00:26:24,680
Those two couldn't have had a key.

247
00:26:25,200 --> 00:26:26,240
It's open.

248
00:26:58,480 --> 00:26:59,920
Officer Ran,

249
00:27:00,000 --> 00:27:03,160
please don't tell anyone
I brought you to the rooftop.

250
00:27:03,240 --> 00:27:05,200
Up there is Mr. Ge's territory.

251
00:27:05,280 --> 00:27:06,720
I can't afford to cross him.

252
00:27:06,800 --> 00:27:08,560
Does Mr. Ge have a key?

253
00:27:08,640 --> 00:27:09,800
Let me tell you.

254
00:27:09,880 --> 00:27:12,640
That old man is Manager Qian's uncle.

255
00:27:12,720 --> 00:27:16,040
But don't worry. The Qian family
is shrewd and tightfisted.

256
00:27:16,640 --> 00:27:17,960
He wouldn't lend out the key.

257
00:27:19,040 --> 00:27:20,240
Alright.

258
00:27:31,760 --> 00:27:32,960
BEIJING TRAVEL

259
00:27:54,960 --> 00:27:57,280
YUXI

260
00:28:08,680 --> 00:28:11,040
RETRIBUTION FOR STEALING CHICKENS

261
00:28:23,480 --> 00:28:25,280
PUBLIC SECURITY

262
00:28:26,160 --> 00:28:28,360
Move it. We've got a homicide.

263
00:28:28,440 --> 00:28:29,360
Stay sharp.

264
00:28:30,280 --> 00:28:31,960
We've searched the 18th floor.

265
00:28:32,040 --> 00:28:33,760
What could we have missed?

266
00:28:33,840 --> 00:28:35,800
Officer Ran is a top graduate of PPSUC.

267
00:28:35,880 --> 00:28:37,840
If he says there's a lead,
there is one for sure.

268
00:29:13,080 --> 00:29:14,440
Something big's going down.

269
00:29:15,040 --> 00:29:16,920
This is where Mr. Ge keeps chickens.

270
00:29:17,000 --> 00:29:18,000
Where are the chickens?

271
00:29:18,080 --> 00:29:20,720
That's exactly the problem.

272
00:29:22,440 --> 00:29:23,400
There's something here.

273
00:29:25,960 --> 00:29:27,680
Officer Qu, over here.

274
00:29:31,920 --> 00:29:33,400
You little rascal.

275
00:29:34,320 --> 00:29:36,520
- I'll beat you to death!
- Don't come closer. I'm a police officer!

276
00:29:48,520 --> 00:29:50,280
Doubao, come in.

277
00:29:50,360 --> 00:29:52,840
What took you so long?

278
00:29:52,920 --> 00:29:56,360
Let go. Let go of my hand.

279
00:29:56,440 --> 00:29:57,640
Come in, Doubao.

280
00:29:57,720 --> 00:29:59,160
Why would I go in?

281
00:29:59,240 --> 00:30:01,600
- Let go.
- I won't!

282
00:30:01,680 --> 00:30:02,560
Get in here.

283
00:30:02,640 --> 00:30:04,120
You killed my chickens!

284
00:30:04,200 --> 00:30:06,400
That's assaulting an officer.
I'm warning you.

285
00:30:09,040 --> 00:30:10,120
Stop!

286
00:30:10,760 --> 00:30:11,920
What took you so long?

287
00:30:12,000 --> 00:30:13,760
I paged you over a dozen times.

288
00:30:14,840 --> 00:30:16,560
Come with me. I'll tell you.

289
00:30:23,520 --> 00:30:24,520
Are you

290
00:30:25,040 --> 00:30:28,080
8233585?

291
00:30:28,840 --> 00:30:30,440
I came to see you.

292
00:30:31,160 --> 00:30:32,880
Good.

293
00:30:32,960 --> 00:30:33,960
I'll be straight with you.

294
00:30:34,040 --> 00:30:37,520
I don't have much to go on.
I only saw it once.

295
00:30:37,600 --> 00:30:38,760
You saw it?

296
00:30:38,840 --> 00:30:40,320
Yeah. I did.

297
00:30:40,400 --> 00:30:41,520
Clear as day.

298
00:30:41,600 --> 00:30:43,160
I saw you too.

299
00:30:43,240 --> 00:30:44,600
Get down!

300
00:30:44,680 --> 00:30:46,640
Get down! Get down now!

301
00:30:46,720 --> 00:30:50,440
Once it's cooked,
it goes straight to the table.

302
00:30:54,360 --> 00:30:55,200
Old man,

303
00:30:56,240 --> 00:30:57,520
I'm here…

304
00:30:59,880 --> 00:31:01,480
Open the door! I'm He Yuanhang.

305
00:31:09,000 --> 00:31:12,160
Sir, I'm here to check the gas.

306
00:31:12,240 --> 00:31:12,920
WEIYANG GAS

307
00:31:13,000 --> 00:31:15,600
Gas inspection? It's inside.

308
00:31:15,680 --> 00:31:16,880
Go check it yourself.

309
00:31:20,080 --> 00:31:22,240
Officer He, you were looking for me?

310
00:31:22,320 --> 00:31:23,600
You paged me, didn't you?

311
00:31:24,200 --> 00:31:26,480
I paged the number
on the missing persons notice.

312
00:31:26,560 --> 00:31:27,920
That's my number.

313
00:31:28,000 --> 00:31:29,320
Who were you talking to just now?

314
00:31:29,400 --> 00:31:31,000
Someone from the gas company.

315
00:31:31,080 --> 00:31:32,280
Gas company?

316
00:31:40,000 --> 00:31:42,520
Officer He! It's me! It's me!

317
00:31:43,480 --> 00:31:44,320
Jin Manlang?

318
00:31:46,120 --> 00:31:47,520
Punk.

319
00:31:49,520 --> 00:31:51,360
Are you here to silence them?

320
00:31:51,440 --> 00:31:52,560
I'm innocent.

321
00:31:52,640 --> 00:31:53,880
I didn't kill anyone.

322
00:31:53,960 --> 00:31:55,160
I didn't mean to cover anything up.

323
00:31:55,240 --> 00:31:56,680
How did you know
I was going to ask about a murder?

324
00:32:03,280 --> 00:32:04,120
Rascal.

325
00:32:04,200 --> 00:32:05,520
You screwed this up.

326
00:32:10,080 --> 00:32:12,720
All 18 chickens had their throats slit,

327
00:32:12,800 --> 00:32:15,360
and now you're turning it around,
saying I'm the killer?

328
00:32:15,960 --> 00:32:16,920
Put that down!

329
00:32:20,840 --> 00:32:22,680
Where are the chickens?

330
00:32:22,760 --> 00:32:24,200
Eighteen victims.

331
00:32:24,280 --> 00:32:25,560
All dumped on the rooftop.

332
00:32:25,640 --> 00:32:27,560
You think I could just
stand by and do nothing?

333
00:32:36,440 --> 00:32:37,720
What are you waiting for?

334
00:32:37,800 --> 00:32:39,840
- Secure the evidence now.
- Alright. Move.

335
00:32:40,720 --> 00:32:41,720
Fangxu.

336
00:32:43,520 --> 00:32:44,360
Next time something like this happens,

337
00:32:44,440 --> 00:32:46,520
shouldn't you call in
the criminal department?

338
00:32:47,120 --> 00:32:48,400
- I…
- I'm not blaming you.

339
00:32:49,080 --> 00:32:51,320
It's fine if I made a wasted trip.

340
00:32:51,840 --> 00:32:53,840
I'm just concerned about how others feel.

341
00:32:53,920 --> 00:32:56,480
After all, everyone showed up
because of you, Officer Ran.

342
00:32:56,560 --> 00:32:57,400
Right?

343
00:33:05,240 --> 00:33:06,720
Sorry about that, Officer Qu.

344
00:33:06,800 --> 00:33:08,440
I caused you trouble.

345
00:33:09,120 --> 00:33:12,720
But these bloodstains
were likely a smokescreen.

346
00:33:12,800 --> 00:33:15,720
It's possible the killer used
chicken blood to cover up human blood.

347
00:33:19,600 --> 00:33:21,520
Officer Qu, we're done.

348
00:33:23,040 --> 00:33:24,520
Alright. Wrap it up.

349
00:33:24,600 --> 00:33:26,480
Take him back for a statement.

350
00:33:39,520 --> 00:33:42,120
Officer Ran, let's go.

351
00:33:43,800 --> 00:33:46,080
You go ahead. I'll collect some samples.

352
00:34:02,800 --> 00:34:05,120
Officer He. Take it easy.

353
00:34:05,200 --> 00:34:06,280
Easy?

354
00:34:06,880 --> 00:34:08,000
I'm innocent, really.

355
00:34:08,080 --> 00:34:09,400
Get in the car.

356
00:34:09,480 --> 00:34:11,080
Eighteen chickens, you know?

357
00:34:11,639 --> 00:34:13,760
I handpicked each of them
and raised them myself.

358
00:34:13,840 --> 00:34:15,320
Don't try anything silly.

359
00:34:15,400 --> 00:34:17,120
Now they're dead for no reason.

360
00:34:17,719 --> 00:34:18,800
You guys get in first.

361
00:34:18,880 --> 00:34:20,679
You'd better get to the bottom of this.

362
00:34:21,280 --> 00:34:24,159
Otherwise, I'm staying
at the station and not leaving.

363
00:34:24,239 --> 00:34:25,159
Get in.

364
00:34:27,920 --> 00:34:30,920
Qu, this case is perfect for you.

365
00:34:31,520 --> 00:34:35,000
Make sure you dig into it properly
and give Mr. Ge a satisfactory answer.

366
00:34:36,000 --> 00:34:37,639
This case suits you too.

367
00:34:37,719 --> 00:34:39,679
He's in handcuffs? Must be serious.

368
00:34:41,040 --> 00:34:42,280
Looks like your temporary transfer
is getting extended.

369
00:34:43,520 --> 00:34:44,800
Will you even make it back?

370
00:34:45,920 --> 00:34:48,320
Well. You're just jealous.

371
00:34:48,400 --> 00:34:49,639
I'm good at what I do.

372
00:34:49,719 --> 00:34:51,400
I can crack any case in a day,
however tough it is.

373
00:34:52,880 --> 00:34:53,920
Han.

374
00:34:54,000 --> 00:34:54,840
Shouhu.

375
00:34:54,920 --> 00:34:57,440
Clear out my desk in six days.

376
00:34:57,520 --> 00:34:59,720
I'll be back on time,
just like Hong Kong, China.

377
00:35:00,440 --> 00:35:02,320
"Good at what I do"? Even
your own apprentice doesn't trust you.

378
00:35:03,280 --> 00:35:05,680
He called me when something happened.

379
00:35:13,200 --> 00:35:18,920
POLICE BY THE PEOPLE
FOR THE PEOPLE

380
00:35:21,400 --> 00:35:22,480
FORENSIC EVIDENCE INTAKE

381
00:35:22,560 --> 00:35:23,400
Sign here.

382
00:35:23,480 --> 00:35:26,920
FORENSIC DEPARTMENT EVIDENCE
TRANSFER FORM, SUBMITTED BY HE YUANHANG

383
00:35:36,800 --> 00:35:38,800
SUBMITTED BY RAN FANGXU

384
00:35:40,600 --> 00:35:42,720
Run the tests as soon as possible.
I'll treat you to a meal later.

385
00:35:46,960 --> 00:35:50,280
I told you. If you dress so elegantly,
you won't catch criminals.

386
00:35:56,960 --> 00:36:00,000
Why are you still standing there?
The suspect's been arrested.

387
00:36:00,080 --> 00:36:01,520
FORENSIC DEPARTMENT

388
00:36:05,520 --> 00:36:06,680
NOTEBOOK

389
00:36:06,760 --> 00:36:10,440
FORENSIC DEPARTMENT
INTERROGATION ROOM

390
00:36:11,920 --> 00:36:17,120
LENIENCY FOR CONFESSION
SEVERITY FOR RESISTANCE

391
00:36:17,200 --> 00:36:20,600
Wolfie, we've known
each other a long time.

392
00:36:20,680 --> 00:36:22,840
I won't need to repeat the rules, right?

393
00:36:22,920 --> 00:36:24,560
No.

394
00:36:28,440 --> 00:36:29,520
Take a look at this.

395
00:36:30,120 --> 00:36:31,120
Start from the beginning.

396
00:36:31,200 --> 00:36:33,120
Who are these two? Where did they go?

397
00:36:37,960 --> 00:36:39,160
MISSING PERSONS

398
00:36:43,680 --> 00:36:47,680
Officer, if you're asking me,
who am I supposed to ask?

399
00:36:47,760 --> 00:36:49,160
I honestly don't know.

400
00:36:51,640 --> 00:36:53,800
Alright. That's enough.

401
00:36:56,640 --> 00:36:57,800
Wrap it up and leave.

402
00:36:58,720 --> 00:37:01,480
Officer He, what are you doing?

403
00:37:01,560 --> 00:37:03,360
Don't be mad.

404
00:37:03,440 --> 00:37:05,960
I'll talk. I'll talk, alright?

405
00:37:57,680 --> 00:38:00,640
Ten thousand in cash upfront.
Another 30,000 after it's done.

406
00:38:01,280 --> 00:38:03,880
The cigarettes are a little extra for you.

407
00:38:07,120 --> 00:38:09,000
You want them laid out or tied up?

408
00:38:09,840 --> 00:38:11,320
I want them gone.
